* 1946, &quot;Other Minds,&quot; &quot;Proceedings of the Aristotelian Society&quot;, Supplementary Volume 20: 148–187. Reprinted in &quot;&quot; 
* 1950, &quot;Truth,&quot; &quot;Proceedings of the Aristotelian Society&quot;, Supplementary Volume 24: 111–128. Reprinted in &quot;&quot; , and in &quot;Proceedings of the Aristotelian Society&quot; &quot;Virtual Issue No. I: Truth&quot; (2013)
* 1953, &quot;How to Talk—some simple ways&quot; &quot;Proceedings of the Aristotelian Society&quot;, 53: 227–246. Reprinted in &quot;&quot; 
* 1954ms, &quot;Unfair to Facts,&quot; in &quot;&quot; 
* 1956a, &quot;Ifs and Cans,&quot; &quot;Proceedings of the British Academy&quot;. Reprinted in &quot;&quot; 
* 1956b, &quot;Performative Utterances,&quot; corrected transcript of an unscripted radio talk delivered in the Third Programme of the BBC. In &quot;&quot; 
* 1957, &quot;A Plea for Excuses: The Presidential Address&quot;, &quot;Proceedings of the Aristotelian Society&quot;, 57: 1–30. Reprinted in &quot;&quot; 
* 1958, &quot;Pretending&quot; &quot;Proceedings of the Aristotelian Society&quot;, Supplementary Volume 32: 261–278. Reprinted in &quot;&quot; 
* 1962, &quot;Performatif-Constatif,&quot; in &quot;Cahiers de Royaumont, Philosophie No. IV, La Philosophie Analytique&quot;, Les Editions de Minuit. 
** Translated in 1963 as &quot;Performative-Constative&quot; by G. J. Warnock, in C. E. Caton ed., &quot;&quot;, University of Illinois Press.
* 1966, &quot;Three Ways of Spilling Ink&quot;, L. W. Forguson (ed.), &quot;The Philosophical Review&quot;, 75 (4): 427–440. Reprinted in &quot;&quot;, 2d ed., ed. W. T. Jones, F. Sontag, M. O. Beckner, and R. J. Fogelin (New York: McGraw Hill Book Co., 1969), and &quot;Philosophical Papers&quot; 1970, 

