In the language of measure theory, Markov&#x27;s inequality states that if is a measure space, formula_6 is a measurable extended real-valued function, and , then

:formula_7

This measure-theoretic definition is sometimes referred to as Chebyshev&#x27;s inequality.

===Extended version for nondecreasing functions===
If is a nondecreasing nonnegative function, is a (not necessarily nonnegative) random variable, and , then

:formula_8

An immediate corollary, using higher moments of supported on values larger than 0, is

