===The uniformly randomized Markov&#x27;s inequality===

If is a nonnegative random variable and , and is a uniformly distributed random variable on formula_10 that is independent of , then

:formula_11

Since is almost surely smaller than one, this bound is strictly stronger than Markov&#x27;s inequality. Remarkably, cannot be replaced by any constant smaller than one, meaning that deterministic improvements to Markov&#x27;s inequality cannot exist in general. While Markov&#x27;s inequality holds with equality for distributions supported on formula_12, the above randomized variant holds with equality for any distribution that is bounded on formula_13.
